The price of commodities is generally stable.
On September 27, Beijing (journalist Dowyan), China News Network, in order to strengthen market regulation before the festival, the Beijing Municipal Markets Regulatory Authority inspected more than 2,000 businesses on the eve of the national holiday.
Inspections show that the market sells food oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, egg milk and other basic necessities, that commodity prices are generally stable, that there are no serious violations and that the market business order is generally stable.
Today, journalists have been informed by the Beijing Municipal Market Supervisory Authority that it conducts a city-wide “integrated law enforcement inspection day”, focusing on priority areas and areas of focus, such as prices, business, QOs, medicines, commerce and all-round law enforcement checks, and comprehensively regulating the market business order.
It was described that the five law enforcement units of the Beijing Municipal Market Supervisory Authority, namely, price, business, Quality Watch, medicine, commerce, etc., were working in tandem and in close cooperation, with the heads of the law enforcement agencies in teams to conduct joint law enforcement inspections of selected randomly selected operators.
During these inspections, law enforcement officials have focused on price behaviour, advertising, food safety, metrology standards, and production safety systems.
Joint law enforcement inspections have also been organized simultaneously by the regional market supervisory authorities, with over 1,600 law enforcement officers, and over 2,000 households of all types of business owners. The inspection shows that the market has sufficient supplies of basic necessities such as food oil, meat, fruits, vegetables and egg milk, that commodity prices are generally stable, that operators are able to operate in compliance with the law, that no serious violations have been detected and that the market business order is generally stable.
