The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) published a report on 26 September that Iran has begun to use advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, further violating the nuclear agreement reached with the world ' s major Powers in 2015.
Comprehensive media reports that the IAEA report states that Iran’s advanced centrifuge at Natanz Nuclear Facility “is accumulating or ready to accumulate enriched uranium.”
Since the withdrawal of United States President Tripp from the nuclear agreement in May last year and the imposition of sanctions on Iran, Iran is gradually violating the restrictions of the nuclear agreement reached with the major Powers in 2015.
The agreement provided that Iran could only use the first generation IR-1 centrifuge to refine uranium.
The other signatories to the agreement, the United Kingdom, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to save the agreement, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
