Tuionetoa was elected as the new Prime Minister of Tonga.
Nukualofa news: The Tongan Parliament of the South Pacific Island State elected the current Minister of Finance and National Planning, Posiva Tuionetoa, as the new Prime Minister of Tonga, replacing the former Prime Minister, Akilisi Posiva, who died of illness earlier this month.
According to the main Tongan media, Matangi website, the Tongan Parliament is unicameral and consists of 26 members.
In the parliamentary vote of the same day, Tuionetoa was defeated by 23 votes against his competitor, Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Infrastructure and Tourism, Semisi Sika, and was successfully elected.
Tonga is a constitutional monarchy with a separation of powers between the executive, legislative and judicial branches.
Tuionetoa is also to be appointed by the King.
The next parliamentary elections will be held in 2021.
