Herake is dead.
On 26 local time, former French President Chirac passed away and was 86 years old.
At a time when the world is in the midst of a century of great change, the many political legacy left behind by this French politician when he came to power still deserves our praise.
Chirac was President of France for 12 years in a very charming manner.
He inherited the diplomatic spirit of de Gaulle independence and independence, as well as his firm support for European integration, and represented the pursuit of the “European dream”.
At the same time, he was a strategic statesman who advocated multipolarity and multilateralism in the world.
That is why the French media judge him as “the distinguished representative of France on the world stage”.
One of the heartening political decisions of Hirac was against the American-led war in Iraq.
Under his leadership, France stood up to the pressure from the United States and was at the forefront of the war.
One year after the war, he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to an intensification of terrorist activities and make the world even more dangerous.
Later, the Chirac warning proved quite right.
At a time when European integration is perplexed and the unilateralism of the United States has become more pronounced, the past has certainly been tempered by the strategic thinking and choices of Chirac in international politics and global affairs.
Chirac is also a French politician who makes Chinese familiar and friendly.
He was one of the proponents and creators of the “Golden Decade” of Chinese-French relations, which, after his first election as President of France in 1995, was driven by the strategic vision of politicians.
In 2004, China established a comprehensive strategic partnership and entered an entirely new phase of bilateral Chinese-French engagement.
During the Chirac administration, bilateral trade between China and France grew rapidly and cooperation between the two countries in a number of areas, including aviation, nuclear energy and rail transport, made groundbreaking progress.
The Middle-French Cultural Year of the Hirac initiative created a completely new cultural exchange pattern in the history of Central-French culture.
Herake's love of Chinese culture has been particularly impressive throughout his life.
According to his Chinese diplomats, Shirak can carry some of Li Bai and Dufu's poems and even make an accurate judgement of the history of Chinese copper.
“Not to look at the pyramid is not really to go to Egypt, not to look at the Qin, not really to China” – the golden phrase comes from Chirac.
“The West has concerns about China's political and social development, the ecological problems arising from China's economic growth, and China's political status at the international level.
But I have full confidence in China.
I believe that China, as a country with a long history of civilization, has sufficient experience to help it build ideas and values for harmonious development and to shoulder its responsibilities on the world stage for a long time. It's not like it's a bad idea.
I also believe that China ' s revival will bring new creative vitality to world culture and enrich it.
The people have gone, but the political legacy and revelation of Chirac left to the world will last forever.
