On 26 September, local time, Wang Yi, State Councillor and Minister for Foreign Affairs, presided over the Foreign Ministers of China and the African States Members of the Security Council at United Nations Headquarters in New York.
The meeting was attended by the Minister for Foreign Affairs of Côte d ' Ivoire, a member of the current African Council, the Minister for Foreign Affairs of Equatorial Guinea, Oyono, the Minister for Foreign Affairs of South Africa, Pandor, and the Minister for Foreign Affairs of Niger, a member designate, Carla, and the Minister for Foreign Affairs of Tunisia, Jesinawi.
Wang Yu has made four recommendations for strengthening cooperation between the Central African parties in the Council.
First, we must work together.
The greatest challenge in the current international situation was unilateralism, the immediate consequence of which was that the basic norms of international relations were being challenged and the role of the United Nations was being undermined to the detriment of developing countries, including African countries, and small and medium-sized countries.
To meet this challenge, Central Africa must stand hand in hand and shoulder to strength.
In the Council, the three African countries speak with one voice, and the focus is not just three votes, but the continent as a whole.
Together, China and Africa will not only be four votes, but will lead others to follow, influence and shape the Council ' s agenda.
Since 2018, China has established a “3+1” coordination mechanism with African members of the Security Council, which needs to be fully utilized.
Secondly, it is through negotiation.
China has always advocated a political solution to the hotspot problem. Africa has a good tradition of consultation and experience of successful good offices by African regional and subregional organizations.
Many of the complex challenges on the Council's agenda, particularly the hotspots in Africa, are mostly rooted in colonialism and, in some cases, directly related to external factors.
Together, we want to use Chapter VI of the United Nations Charter to play the role of good offices, mediation, etc.
Thirdly, self-empowerment.
African countries and peoples know their problems best, and Africa has the capacity and wisdom to solve its problems.
The Council should focus on listening to and respecting the will of Africa when dealing with hot spots in Africa, should play the role of regional and subregional organizations and should encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa.
China is ready to strengthen its coordination with non-governmental organizations and to firmly promote capacity-building for African-owned peace operations.
Fourthly, development is fundamental.
China and the vast majority of African countries are developing countries, and we insist on putting economic and social development first and supporting each other in their chosen development path.
China would like to align the establishment of a “one-way street” with the AU Agenda 2063, the United Nations Agenda for Sustainable Development 2030 and the development strategies of African countries, in order to help African countries to strengthen their development capacities and address the root causes of conflict.
Together, we want to promote greater United Nations investment in Africa ' s development.
China has provided and will continue to provide all possible human and material assistance to the Democratic Republic of the Congo as a result of the renewed outbreak of the Ebola epidemic, and is ready to coordinate its efforts with African countries to mobilize the United Nations, WHO and others to enhance their assistance in order to fulfil the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
Newborns, etc. relays save small lives.
Surprise!
Mothers of second-born babies had an early onset, and on their way to the hospital in a panic, a 32-week premature baby was born on Dad's car driver.
Fortunately, obstetrics and newborns were treated in a timely manner and the relays saved this little life.
By chance, on 19, 20 and 21 days, the maternity and neonatal sections of the Hubei provincial maternal and child health centre received three premature births on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in 120 first aid trucks, both 29 weeks.
At 7 a.m. on 19 September, Ms. Cheng, a second-born pregnant mother, felt a little tummy pain and thought that she was 32 weeks pregnant and that the first one was premature, and she packed up the items to be delivered and was ready to take a shower and go straight to the hospital.
At 9:30, Ms. Cheng packed and asked her husband to drive from Seo Dong ' s home to the hospital.
I didn't expect the baby to be born in Dad's car co-pilot soon after the car opened.
After 20 minutes, Ms. Cheng and the baby finally arrived at the maternity and obstetrics building at the Hubei Health Centre for Women and Children.
The hospital security officers saw the husband and wife and the baby who were in a state of panic and immediately informed the maternity ward, and the Deputy Medical Doctor Zhang Jian and the midwife Liu Ying, who were waiting for four doctors, carrying their bags and cords, stormed downstairs.
“At the time, the mother was lying on the side of the car, under the water of sheep and blood, with a baby boy standing next to her, with an umbilical cord. It's not like it's a bad idea.
Zhang Chau enquired about the fact that the baby was a 32-week premature child, that parents on their way had not been able to cover the package, that the early autumn morning had been cold, that he had frozen his skin pale, that he had no crying, and that his limbs had collapsed.
Yoo Ying went to the co-pilot to process the baby's umbilical cord, Zhang Jing went into the cab, quickly opened the delivery bag, provided the child with the inside healing towels and the handbags to keep the baby warm on several floors, and cleaned the newborns' respiratory tracts (e.g. graphs), then carried the baby up to the 12th floor of the neonatal unit.
Upon receiving the news, the Neonatal Medical Officer arrived at the nurse ' s station to rescue the premature baby.
At the time, the baby had a purple color and suffered from a lack of oxygen asphyxiation, and the doctor immediately inducted him with a trachea, less than a minute later, the baby recovered its heart rate and gradually recovered its skin color and recovered successfully.
After admission to hospital, the 32-week-old baby was placed in a respirator, which, after sustained rescue and steady breathing, was successfully evacuated the following day.
After a week of treatment, the baby ' s vital signs are now stable and breathing well and a small amount of breastfeeding has begun.
On the 19th, 20th and 21st days, three premature births on the road were attended by the obstetrics and newborns section of the hospital, and the other two were born on 120 first aid trucks, all 29 weeks of premature births, which are currently being actively treated in the neonatal section.
The Director of Obstetrics at the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Institute, Sun Guoqiang, explained that in recent years, mothers and children in the province have received many babies born in subways and private cars, a situation that may threaten the lives of mothers and children.
The Director reminded that pregnant mothers should come to the hospital as soon as they had abdominal pain, broken water and seen red.
In the event that she is in the home or on the road, the mother should make every effort to be in bed, with blankets, etc., under her hips to prevent the baby from coming out and hitting the ground, and the child should be warmed immediately and brought to the hospital as soon as possible.
