She has only been absent for one shift in three years, and the “missing amount” amounts to several Australian dollars.
He states that Ms. Ayton was dismissed “in fact unrelated to her conduct or behaviour”.
He said, “It seems to me that the real reason why Mr. Wang should dismiss her was that he preferred to hire staff with an Asian background, supported by evidence of an advertisement.
According to section 772(f) of the Fair Work Act, Mr. Wang ' s conduct appears to constitute a violation of the anti-discrimination law and/or dismissal of the applicant is unlawful. It's not like it's a bad idea.
