After the outbreak, Chinese consumers are shifting from eating pork to other animal proteins, which has led the authorities to destroy many herds. Over the past year, China ' s number of raw pigs has been halved and the price of pork almost doubled.
China produces and consumes two thirds of the world ' s pork.
The Senior Animal Protein Analyst Pan (Chenjun Pan, an interpreter) in the China region of the Dutch Cooperative Bank states that demand for other meat, including beef, has increased, and that China, the world’s largest animal protein importer, currently imports 27% of pork and 24% of beef.
Ms. Pan said that China ' s imports of beef from Australia had increased by 65 per cent in the first half of the year, and China had surpassed the United States and Japan and had become Australia ' s largest export market for beef.
