The Press Office of the State Council issued a White Paper on China and the World in a New Era
On the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the establishment of the People ' s Republic of China, the Press Office of the State Council issued a White Paper entitled " China and the World in a New Era " .
The Deputy Minister of China and Director of the Press Office of the State Council, Xu Xuan, stated that the White Paper focused on “Where China comes from and goes” and “What kind of world China promotes” and “How China develops with the world” by providing a systematic account of China's development achievements, development paths and trends, as well as an in-depth account of China's relations with the world in order to improve the international community's understanding and understanding of China's development.
The White Paper states that for 70 years, under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, China has undergone dramatic changes, creating a miracle of development unprecedented in human history, particularly since the eighteenth anniversary of the Party, when China ' s development achieved historic achievements and changes.
Through a wealth of data and facts, the White Paper describes the great achievements, significance and world contribution of China ' s development over the past 70 years.
The White Paper states that China has gone through centuries of development in developed countries, and that the economy is the second largest in the world. Nearly 1.4 billion people have escaped material shortages and have generally reached a level of prosperity with unprecedented dignity and rights.
The White Paper emphasizes that for 70 years, the Chinese people have worked for nothing, self-reliance and hard work to bring about a new world; for 70 years, China has developed in its interaction with the world, embracing the world, learning from it and contributing to it; and for 70 years, China has contributed to world peace while achieving self-development and has injected momentum into the common development of all countries.
The White Paper states that, for 70 years, China ' s development has been successful essentially because, under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, the Chinese people have found the correct path of China ' s socialism and have steadfastly followed it.
The White Paper emphasizes that China ' s specialist socialist path is a path that has been set out in the national context, a path that places the interests of the people first, a path to reform and innovation, a path to common development in an open world and a path to a State that is fully governed by the rule of law.
This path of development in China, in line with China ' s national circumstances and in keeping with the demands of the times, will increasingly show bright development prospects as the times move forward.
In response to the concerns of the international community about China ' s development, the White Paper emphasizes that the realization of the country ' s wealth, national renewal and the well-being of its people are the dream of both the Chinese people and the common dream of all peoples.
The White Paper states that China is the main stabilizer and engine of world economic growth, that all-round openness creates more opportunities for development in all countries, that China provides more public goods to the international community, that China ' s development provides experience and lessons to other developing countries, and that China will never follow the path of “national domination”.
Faced with the age of “what is happening in the world and what human beings do”, the White Paper states that today's world is in the midst of a century of great change and that human society is both hopeful and challenging.
China has proposed the formation of a community of human destiny and a new path of cooperation for win-win and shared development, offering new options for human development.
The White Paper calls on States to unite in the construction of new international relations, the promotion of new forms of economic globalization, the preservation of the international system, with the United Nations at its core, the promotion of the exchange of ideas among civilizations, the joint promotion of a community of human destiny and a better world.
With China ' s growing development, the international community is generally concerned about how the developing China can live with the world.
The White Paper states that China ' s development is indispensable to the world and to its peaceful development, prosperity and stability.
China has always placed its own development at the forefront of human development. China has insisted on cooperation for win-win and joint development. It has insisted on preserving and promoting economic globalization. It has actively developed a global partnership. It has firmly supported multilateralism and international justice. It has also promoted high-quality development in the “one-way street”. It has actively participated in leading the reform and construction of the global system of governance. It has always been a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development and a guardian of international order.
China is now entering a new era of development.
The White Paper states that China in the new era will not change its resolve to follow China’s special socialist path, to learn from each other, to cooperate and win, and to join hands with the world.
The White Paper concludes by stating that the future of nations in today ' s world has never been so closely linked.
The White Paper, China and the World in a New Era, consists of a preface, text and concluding remarks, with more than 29,000 words.
The White Paper is published in eight languages, namely, Chinese, English, French, Russian, German, Spanish, A.J., and is published by People ' s Press and Foreign Press, respectively, and distributed in Xinhua Bookshops throughout the country.
