A villager hunting wild animals in Paukang County in Hubei was ordered to "compulsory mountain patrol."
A villager in Hubei Bokang County was sentenced for hunting wild animals and was ordered to pay compensation of $15,420 for the cost of repairing the environmental damage to ecological resources (RMB, same as).
Due to the poverty of the accused ' s family, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office used alternative labour to compensate for the cost of ecological restoration, thus achieving an organic harmonization of legal and social effects.
On the 27th day, Wang Zhonglang, Deputy Prosecutor-General of the Poucon District Public Prosecutor's Office, described the fact that, through alternative labour such as 3 months of “compulsory mountain patrols”, the accused had established deep feelings with the wild monkeys and was deeply responsible for the previous animal hunting.
On 21 June this year, a criminal incidental civil service action in the area of ecological resources was filed by the District Prosecutor ' s Office of Paukang, which was heard in public court and sentenced in court.
The accused was sentenced to three years ' imprisonment and four years ' probation and a fine of $3,000, and was ordered to pay $15420 for environmental damage to ecological resources.
It was found that Zhou had installed an electrical grid at the cliffs in late January 2014, hunting more than 20 wild animals, including euphemisms, twigs and furs.
Antelopes belong to the endangered wild animals of the second national level, and small euphemisms and furs are listed in the National List of Land-based Wildlife Protection.
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his unlawful facts and conduct and was willing to assume incidental civil liability.
However, in view of the poor financial situation of one family member in the week, the local village council, the forest station and the three parties in the week, in coordination with the Public Prosecutor ' s Office of the county of Paukang, have reached an agreement on alternative labour to compensate for the cost of ecological restoration: i.e., the provision of public goods to cover the cost of ecological rehabilitation through a one-year training and maintenance of monkeys in the village ' s monkey reserve.
In response to the Prosecutor's recommendation, the Court accepted that the obligation of “alternative labour to compensate for ecological rehabilitation” should be actively fulfilled, while at the same time granting a suspended sentence.
At present, Zhou Zhou Zhou has worked for three months in the Monkey Reserve and is active and performing well.
In recent years, the Prosecutor ' s Office of the county of Paoucon has in practice integrated the functions of prosecution and social governance. Scientificly, by means of oversight, such as prosecutorial recommendations, investigative supervision and procedural supervision, the ecological damage caused by criminal acts has been minimized by judicial means.
