Trade-related frictions affect the United States economy's “checklist”.
The United States economic “pay card” for the second quarter of this year shows that the United States gross domestic product (GDP) grew at a significantly slower rate than in the previous quarter, affected by a sharp decline in private sector investment and exports.
Analysts noted that economic and trade frictions and the resulting uncertainty were the main causes of the decline in private sector investment and exports in the second quarter.
The final revised data released by the US Department of Commerce on 26 June show that US GDP grew at an annual rate of 2% in the second quarter, which is the same as the revision data published earlier, but is significantly below 3.1% in the first quarter.
The data show that consumption growth is the main factor underpinning the growth of the United States economy in the second quarter.
Individual consumption spending, which accounts for about 70 per cent of the total economy of the United States, increased by 4.6 per cent in the current season, boosting economic growth by 3.03 percentage points.
In addition, government consumption expenditure and investment boosted growth by 0.82 percentage points.
However, private sector investment declined by 6.3% in the second quarter compared to the previous quarter, slowing down growth by 1.16 percentage points in the current quarter; exports declined by 5.7 percentage points compared to the previous quarter, and net exports slowed down growth by 0.68 percentage points in the current quarter.
According to Barry Knap, the management partner of Einsideside Macroeconomics Consulting in the United States, private sector investment has not only failed to maintain the momentum of last year ' s growth, but has declined sharply, owing to the impact of increased trade friction and uncertainty on business confidence.
According to Knap, United States corporate capital spending is expected to remain declining next year, influenced by policy uncertainty.
Analysts argue that, while consumption growth has strongly supported the United States economy in the second quarter, there are growing indications that trade and trade friction and the uncertainty it creates have affected consumer confidence and adversely affected United States consumption prospects.
The survey leader, Richard Cortin, Professor of Economics at the University of Michigan, had recently indicated that, in a recent survey, 38 per cent of consumers had spontaneously referred to the negative effects of tariffs on the United States economy, a percentage that had been high for a year and a half.
With regard to future economic developments in the United States, analysts generally believe that the United States economy will continue to slow down.
However, it was also suggested that if trade and economic friction were eased, the performance of the United States industrial sector and financial markets would improve.
The British Economist think tank global economist, Karin Burch, predicts that in the future the United States economy will continue its downward trend since the beginning of the year and that the rate of growth will fall to a lower level than in the second quarter.
Mark Zandy, the chief economist for Moody’s Analysis, predicts that, assuming that economic and trade friction does not continue to escalate, the US economy will grow by 2.3% this year, slowing further to 1.6% next year.
Ellen Hazen, investment manager of Patnam Investment, stated that the greatest concern of the enterprise today is economic and trade disputes and the uncertainty they bring, which, if resolved, would be significantly reduced and the industrial sector would perform much better.
According to Matt Melly, stock strategist in Miller-Tabak Asset Management, economic and trade frictions remain a “prior problem” and are the main cause of the large volatility of US capital markets this year, and their proper resolution will be the key to influencing the direction of US capital markets for the rest of the year.
The first joint parental leave for couples in Ningxia is 10 days per year for parents aged 0 to 3 years
Ensuring the legitimate rights and interests of women is an expression of respect for and guarantee of human rights and an important sign of the progress of civil society.
On 27 September, at the fifteenth session of the Standing Committee of the 12th People ' s Congress of the Ningxia-Region Autonomous Region, the Regulation on the Protection of the Rights and Interests of Women of the Ningxia-Region Autonomous Region was adopted.
This is the local regulation issued by the first province of Ningxia for the protection of women ' s legitimate rights and interests in a comprehensive and systematic manner and will be implemented as of 1 November 2019.
It is understood that the Regulations adopted on this occasion were amended on the basis of the 2007 Ningxia Measures for the Implementation of the Law of the People's Republic of China on the Protection of the Rights and Interests of Women and are divided into 9 chapters, article 65, which includes general principles, political rights, cultural and educational rights and interests, labour and social security rights and interests, property rights and interests, personal rights, marital and family rights and interests, legal responsibilities and by-laws.
In the Ordinance, Ningxia encouraged the exploration of joint parental leave, which was the first in the country.
In April this year, the Office of the State Council issued a Directive on the Promotion of the Development of Care Services for Children and Adolescents under the Age of Three, which contains a description of joint parenthood.
In the course of the revision of the Regulations, Ningxia introduced an innovation that “encourages employers to give joint parental leave for 10 days each year between the ages of 0 and 3 years to couples who have children in accordance with the law and regulations”.
At the same time, the Ordinance highlights the fight against sexual harassment and the protection of female minors.
Article 43 of the Regulations incorporates the latest legislative results from the current personal status code of the Chinese Civil Code, detailing the constituent elements of sexual harassment, the main subjects and mechanisms against sexual harassment, etc.
Article 44 of the Ordinance explicitly prohibits the occurrence of sexual abuse against girls and requires educational institutions to carry out the relevant educational, protective and preventive work as a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
With regard to women ' s right to know and dispose of marital and family property, article 35 of the Ordinance clearly defines women ' s right to know and the obligations of property registers and related subjects, providing strong institutional support for women ' s defence of their rights.
Moreover, in response to the social hotspots – gender discrimination in employment – section 26 of the Ordinance prohibits not only direct discrimination, but also indirect discrimination, and draws on recent experience in joint interviews, strengthens penalties for gender-based discrimination offences, and strengthens the defence of women’s legitimate rights and interests.
In recent years, the Ningxia Women ' s Union ' s Joint Public Prosecutor ' s Office, Civil Administration and others have been very effective in promoting and introducing social and professional involvement in the mediation of marital and family disputes and in combating domestic violence.
This is summarized and promoted in the Regulations, which in several articles encourage the mobilization of social forces, the pooling of social resources to defend women ' s rights and interests, and require people ' s governments above the county level to provide stable and institutional guarantees and support, including through the purchase of services.
