The Minister of Finance, Liu Qun, and 67 financial institutions have transferred $860.1 billion to fund the Social Security Fund.
The Minister of Finance, Liu Qun 27, stated that to date, 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions had completed the transfer of part of the State-owned capital to the Social Security Fund, bringing the total value of the transferred State-owned capital to approximately $860.1 billion.
Liu Quin made this statement at a national mission to transfer part of the State-owned capital for the work of the Social Security Fund, which was organized by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security and the National Finance Commission.
“The transfer of part of the State-owned capital to the Social Security Fund is an important initiative to reform and improve the basic pension insurance system. It is a full expression of universal ownership of the results of State-owned enterprise development and of the intergenerational equity of the basic pension insurance system. It is an immediate and long-term policy measure. It's not like it's a bad idea.
In 2017, the State Council issued the Programme for the Transfer of Partial State Capital to the Implementation of the Social Security Fund, which calls for the selection of some central enterprises and some provinces for piloting.
According to Liu Quan, the transition process had yielded positive results.
At the central level, three transfers of 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have been completed, totalling approximately 8,60.1 billion yuan.
Of these, the transfer of central financial institutions from the Ministry of Finance to carry out the responsibility of financiers has largely been completed.
Central enterprise conversions have taken place on a certain scale.
At the local level, the transition from enterprise to enterprise continues.
By the end of 2018, pilot projects in Zhejiang and Yunnan provinces had been largely completed, transferring State capital of $15.8 billion and $18.5 billion respectively.
In addition to the pilot provinces, preparatory work for the transition has been carried out successively in other provinces, laying the groundwork for further implementation.
According to a joint circular issued by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the National Council of Finance, the General Tax Administration and the CSR, the transfer of part of the State-owned capital to the Social Security Fund was fully rolled out in 2019 and substantially completed by 2020.
