The Hong Kong government has launched a free special training program to help financially affected employees to survive.
The HKSAR Government announced on 27 January that it would introduce a free special training programme for employees who have recently been affected by the economic situation, and that eligible trainees would receive a maximum training allowance of HK$4,000 per month upon completion of the course.
