Journalists have been informed by the Jiangxi Province Road Transport Authority that, to date, 1,334 passenger lines have been established in 11 established municipalities and 6 directly administered districts in Jiangxi.
The Head of the Road Transport Authority of Jiangxi Province described the security situation of road passenger transport as critical, owing to the formality of the safety management of some passenger enterprises, the lack of accountability of the enterprise ' s safety agents, the frequent occurrence of irregularities such as speeding and exhausting driving of passenger vehicles.
In order to further reduce the overall responsibility of road passenger transport enterprises for safe production and safe travel of passengers by road, Jiangxi began piloting the Long Line System in 2017 and gradually extending it throughout the province in 2018.
Currently, 92 road passenger enterprises in Jiangxi have implemented the “wirelong” system, with 1334 lines for the “wiremaster” management, covering 4824 passenger vehicles.
It was described that the “wirelonger” is generally the responsibility of the road transport company, which designates specialized personnel, specifically responsible for the management of the lines concerned, persons, vehicles, lines, etc., to ensure the overall control of the lines, vehicles, drivers, operating environments, etc., and to ensure the safe operation of the lines.
